rik, Lars, Nils, Sven, Alvar, Anders, Aslaug, Astrid, Helmer, Jarl, Knut, Sigfrid.","Swedish (<b>Ström</b>) and Danish (<b>Strøm</b>): from <i>ström</i>, <i>strøm</i> ‘current’, a topographic name for someone who lived by a river or a stream, or an ornamental name. Compare   Stream   2,   Strome  , and   Strum  .","Norwegian (<b>Strøm</b>): habitational name from any of numerous farmsteads so named from Old Norse <i>straumr</i> ‘current, stream’. Compare 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Rycharde","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A male name; and also found as a female name in one parish in Devon. It is merely another spelling of Richard."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705205,"age":9,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":11,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":25,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":27,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":40,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705212,"age":60,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Rycharde Streame was born in 1560, in Buckinghamshire, England, his father, John Streame I, was 20 and his mother, Anne Vincent, was 20. He had at least 1 daughter with Mary Magdeline Sirett Claudy. He died in 1629, in Fleet, Dorset, England, at the age of 69."},"et":{"1560–1629":"1560–1629","1560–1624":"1560–1624","1560–1601":"1560–1601","1585–1622":"1585–1622","1540–1618":"1540–1618","1540–1612":"1540–1612","1560":"1560","April 1618":"aprill 1618","1571":"1571","20 May 1601":"20. mai 1601","1569":"1569","1624":"1624","1612":"1612","1601":"1601","1600":"1600","1622":"1622","Abt. 1612":"umbes 1612","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1629":"1629","1618":"1618","19 November 1622":"19. november 1622","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshir